Asymptomatic patients should generally not be screened for thyroid disease (exceptions
include pregnant, post-partum, or post-menopausal women). Thyroid function in patients
with suspected thyroid disease is best assessed with TSH as the sole screening test. It is
not appropriate to order free-T4 and/or free-T3 in addition to TSH in the initial screen.
